      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i guess i'm worried the reviewers will think the data is just messy or that there's some unobserved variable creating a lot of error. if i want to explain that the 'noise' isn't just random chance but maybe something more structural or chaotic in the sampling process, what's the best way to phrase that without sounding unscientific?",
