      "content": "that makes sense. saying \"unmodeled heterogeneity\" sounds a lot more professional. do you think i should lean into the idea that these \"unobserved variables\" might be causing patterns that look chaotic or unpredictable? like, how do i characterize the influence of these hidden factors if they seem to disrupt the expected stability of the results?",
